WEBVTT

00:29.217 --> 00:30.302
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

00:33.388 --> 00:35.014
CHARACTERS, EVENTS, ORGANIZATIONS,
AND PLACES IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

00:35.015 --> 00:36.308
ALL CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
FILMED IN A SAFE ENVIRONMENT

01:35.117 --> 01:37.911
But why would you say liking me

01:38.954 --> 01:40.622
is being greedy?

01:41.206 --> 01:42.708
Because you'll go back soon?

01:43.500 --> 01:45.544
It doesn't matter if I'm being greedy now.

01:48.004 --> 01:49.673
I can't stop my feelings anyway.

01:52.717 --> 01:54.343
So I'll just keep going,

01:54.344 --> 01:56.888
because I don't want
to waste our time together.

01:59.724 --> 02:02.727
Then don't say
you're being greedy anymore.

02:03.270 --> 02:04.563
If you say that again,

02:05.480 --> 02:06.898
I won't let it slide.

02:08.358 --> 02:09.734
I should be careful, then.

02:14.573 --> 02:16.366
EPISODE 8

02:18.243 --> 02:20.161
Stop staring at it.

02:20.162 --> 02:21.955
It won't even be visible tomorrow.

02:23.373 --> 02:26.167
Oh. And make sure to call your grandma.

02:26.168 --> 02:28.545
She'll be worried sick
after you left like that.

02:29.629 --> 02:31.715
I will.

02:34.760 --> 02:36.636
I used to be just like that watch.

02:38.096 --> 02:42.100
I was frozen in time,
but someone made time move again for me.

02:42.726 --> 02:43.810
Like this.

02:49.357 --> 02:53.904
So how about letting time with your dad
start moving again?

02:58.533 --> 03:00.202
The past is the past.

03:00.744 --> 03:01.787
What's important

03:02.871 --> 03:04.581
is the time that will flow from now on.

03:27.395 --> 03:29.688
Her boyfriend died back then.

03:29.689 --> 03:32.775
He went to study in Boston,
but he suddenly died.

03:32.776 --> 03:33.984
Hey, roomie.

03:33.985 --> 03:37.906
The fact that I lived
while he died from that accident…

03:38.740 --> 03:40.325
It's a good thing you took it out.

03:41.201 --> 03:44.620
I want someone to have joy in their life.

03:44.621 --> 03:48.166
She was a grateful disruption
that made me live again.

03:52.003 --> 03:53.630
Mr. Park, we…

03:54.381 --> 03:56.466
Of course. I know.

04:04.891 --> 04:06.434
Take her home safely.

04:07.978 --> 04:10.105
Let's go, Genius.

04:31.042 --> 04:32.043
Go on in.

04:34.921 --> 04:36.130
Bye.

04:38.550 --> 04:40.718
Look forward.

04:40.719 --> 04:42.803
It'll be dangerous
if you fall down the hill.

04:48.643 --> 04:50.186
I'm relieved.

04:51.354 --> 04:52.355
You're warm.

04:53.231 --> 04:54.649
It's just that…

04:55.775 --> 04:56.985
this feels like a dream.

04:58.486 --> 04:59.905
I can't believe it.

05:09.205 --> 05:10.873
Should I make this feel more real?

05:10.874 --> 05:12.249
No, thanks.

05:14.002 --> 05:15.837
I'll go now. Head inside.

05:16.421 --> 05:17.464
Get back safely.

05:35.607 --> 05:36.650
What a relief.

05:45.867 --> 05:48.369
Now, now.

05:48.370 --> 05:50.580
You didn't take your meds again?

05:52.165 --> 05:55.167
I told you to take them on time.

05:55.168 --> 05:57.795
Let's go to the hospital this week.

05:57.796 --> 06:01.383
Keep your cardiac enzyme
test results in your wallet

06:02.258 --> 06:05.804
so someone can see it if you ever collapse
when you're not with me.

06:06.429 --> 06:07.430
We have to go, okay?

06:08.056 --> 06:11.392
Just think of me as a nagging son,

06:11.393 --> 06:13.478
and come with me.

06:14.396 --> 06:15.729
All right.

06:15.730 --> 06:16.856
And you

06:17.524 --> 06:20.235
should think of me
as a father who listens to you,

06:20.860 --> 06:22.696
so tell me anything

06:23.655 --> 06:26.031
that you have a hard time
telling anyone else.

06:26.032 --> 06:28.159
You can tell me
anything that troubles you.

06:29.911 --> 06:31.830
I'll be your safe space.

06:34.708 --> 06:37.710
I wasn't trying to hide
my relationship with Ms. Song…

06:37.711 --> 06:39.129
You really like her, right?

06:43.633 --> 06:45.260
- Yes.
- All right.

06:46.094 --> 06:50.514
Let her feel joy again.

06:50.515 --> 06:55.394
You don't need a reason
to want someone to be happy.

06:55.395 --> 06:58.773
As long as you're sincere, it's okay.

07:06.030 --> 07:08.074
Ms. Song,
there's an international delivery.

07:14.080 --> 07:15.081
Wow.

07:17.125 --> 07:19.543
I finally got the sketch sample
for my design.

07:19.544 --> 07:20.795
Make some noise!

07:23.381 --> 07:24.966
It's all thanks to this pen.

07:36.019 --> 07:38.897
But how did you come up
with the idea of sending me a pen?

07:41.941 --> 07:45.361
I kept thinking about how you said
you felt like you were trapped.

07:48.656 --> 07:50.200
I used to feel that way, too.

07:51.367 --> 07:54.579
Back then, I kept thinking the same thing.

08:00.210 --> 08:01.503
If…

08:02.170 --> 08:05.006
there was just a small crack
to breathe through, I could live.

08:06.674 --> 08:07.675
But…

08:08.176 --> 08:11.179
that "if" never came true for me.

08:12.555 --> 08:14.431
I guess I wanted

08:14.432 --> 08:16.601
that pen to be that "if" for you.

08:19.145 --> 08:21.564
Chan understands me so well…

08:23.441 --> 08:25.777
Sorry, I was rambling.

08:26.986 --> 08:28.196
I should go now.

08:39.165 --> 08:40.959
-  Great work today.
-  You too.

08:42.043 --> 08:44.419
- I'm going back to Korea first.
- Okay, sure.

08:54.347 --> 08:57.558
Maybe it's because I lost
the pen I used for seven years,

08:57.559 --> 09:00.186
but I couldn't sketch anything
during the two days here.

09:01.146 --> 09:03.897
Yes, seven years ago. Early July.

09:03.898 --> 09:06.150
And the engraving is Haran.

09:06.151 --> 09:07.442
One second.

09:07.443 --> 09:11.614
Uh, yeah. We have the model name
and the engraving design on file.

09:23.459 --> 09:25.044
The past is the past.

09:26.129 --> 09:27.505
What's important…

09:33.303 --> 09:35.263
is the time
that will flow from now on.

09:41.311 --> 09:43.229
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

09:45.648 --> 09:46.815
Grandma.

09:48.067 --> 09:50.152
Where have you been?

09:50.153 --> 09:51.904
I was at a meeting.

09:51.905 --> 09:53.363
Our dinner ended late.

09:53.364 --> 09:54.991
A meeting dressed like this?

09:55.825 --> 09:57.326
And what's this…

09:57.327 --> 09:58.369
I'll do it.

09:58.912 --> 10:00.622
I'm tired. I'm going to bed.

10:01.998 --> 10:03.582
Grandma, did you go to Seongsu…

10:03.583 --> 10:06.001
I'm sorry, but just let this go for now.

10:06.002 --> 10:07.128
Please.

10:08.922 --> 10:09.964
What?

10:11.007 --> 10:12.299
I just…

10:12.300 --> 10:15.886
thought we haven't been
talking much lately.

10:15.887 --> 10:18.264
Are you sure nothing's wrong?

10:18.890 --> 10:21.767
What's wrong is you asking questions
when I'm so sleepy.

10:21.768 --> 10:23.311
Go to bed.

10:23.978 --> 10:26.231
All right. Good night.

10:32.612 --> 10:34.030
Why are her shoes like that?

10:35.990 --> 10:37.533
It couldn't have been a meeting.

10:40.161 --> 10:41.663
Where in the world was she?

10:54.425 --> 10:57.512
EXAMINATION

11:17.907 --> 11:19.367
The door is closing.

11:20.118 --> 11:22.119
Let me get on!

11:22.120 --> 11:23.620
Thank you.

11:34.340 --> 11:35.549
What's that?

11:35.550 --> 11:38.468
He's the definition of neatness,
and he's got bedhead?

11:38.469 --> 11:40.805
Okay,
I'll check and email you.

11:47.895 --> 11:50.773
He's late and has bedhead? Mr. Yeon?

11:51.941 --> 11:54.484
What's going on?
That doesn't suit him at all.

11:55.570 --> 11:57.195
Look. Isn't it crazy?

11:57.196 --> 11:58.864
- This is insane.
- Is this for real?

11:58.865 --> 12:00.407
Sorry! What are you up to?

12:00.408 --> 12:03.160
Hayeong! Seunggyu took a rare photo.

12:03.161 --> 12:04.536
What photo?

12:04.537 --> 12:07.539
I was organizing the photos
I took during my trend research…

12:07.540 --> 12:09.583
and I was shocked.

12:09.584 --> 12:11.878
That stiff, uptight Mr. Yeon is dating?

12:12.587 --> 12:16.131
This is crazy!

12:16.132 --> 12:18.759
But they look so good together.

12:18.760 --> 12:19.843
They do.

12:21.763 --> 12:22.847
How shameless.

12:23.556 --> 12:25.515
Why is she being so loud when she's late?

12:25.516 --> 12:27.727
Hey, look.

12:31.022 --> 12:32.774
She's the head of La Mode Eclat,

12:33.358 --> 12:36.068
and that's the co-head and her husband.

12:36.069 --> 12:38.278
Oh, geez.

12:38.279 --> 12:40.989
Seunggyu! They were just having
a business meeting.

12:40.990 --> 12:44.618
So they were the heads
of La Mode Eclat.

12:46.662 --> 12:49.248
Sorry about that.

12:51.376 --> 12:53.668
Oh, dear. Why is she suddenly whistling?

12:53.669 --> 12:55.295
There's no in-between with her.

12:56.964 --> 12:57.965
He's right.

12:58.633 --> 12:59.926
Why am I relieved?

13:00.885 --> 13:02.177
But I wonder if Mr. Yeon

13:02.178 --> 13:04.805
would still have that default expression
when he's dating.

13:04.806 --> 13:07.182
No way. I'm sure he'll be different.

13:07.183 --> 13:11.896
He might be
really sweet to the woman he likes.

13:12.480 --> 13:14.523
Sweet?

13:22.615 --> 13:23.698
Your hand.

13:23.699 --> 13:25.660
You might slip
since you're wearing heels.

13:28.830 --> 13:32.499
This happened to my friend,

13:32.500 --> 13:33.667
uh…

13:33.668 --> 13:36.002
but this guy

13:36.003 --> 13:40.173
brushed off dry leaves in the dirt
with his bare hands so she wouldn't slip.

13:40.174 --> 13:41.883
What does that mean?

13:41.884 --> 13:43.052
With his bare hands?

13:43.636 --> 13:44.719
That's love.

13:44.720 --> 13:45.888
Love?

13:46.806 --> 13:50.100
Then if the woman cried,

13:50.101 --> 13:53.436
and he looked at her with pity
and wiped her tears with his hand,

13:53.437 --> 13:55.313
what does that mean?

13:57.024 --> 13:58.108
Love.

13:58.109 --> 14:00.026
He loves me?

14:00.027 --> 14:02.737
And the fact that
you're overanalyzing his every move

14:02.738 --> 14:04.698
means you like him too.

14:04.699 --> 14:06.741
No, that wasn't about me.

14:06.742 --> 14:08.034
That was my friend.

14:08.035 --> 14:09.494
It's obvious it was about you.

14:09.495 --> 14:12.247
My friend told me during a school reunion.

14:12.248 --> 14:13.331
You liar.

14:13.332 --> 14:14.375
Ms. Song Hayeong.

14:16.169 --> 14:18.170
- The new material you mentioned…
-  Ah.

14:18.171 --> 14:20.256
Uh… Mmm…

14:23.634 --> 14:24.968
Hello?

14:24.969 --> 14:26.636
Yes, hello.

14:26.637 --> 14:29.181
I just got an urgent call.

14:29.182 --> 14:30.724
Are you busy right now?

14:30.725 --> 14:31.726
I'm busy too.

14:38.149 --> 14:40.067
What should I say when I give this to her?

14:48.492 --> 14:49.577
Hmm?

14:53.873 --> 14:56.334
Hey, you said
you're coming in the evening.

14:57.001 --> 14:58.376
I'm meeting someone here.

14:58.377 --> 15:00.003
Goodness.

15:00.004 --> 15:01.296
You mean with me?

15:02.840 --> 15:04.424
She's meeting me!

15:04.425 --> 15:07.677
- Hmm?
- What? This is so sudden.

15:07.678 --> 15:10.180
Something came up,
so she's returning to Mungyeong today.

15:10.181 --> 15:12.600
Wow. You were going to meet without me?

15:13.100 --> 15:15.018
- You're always leaving me out.
-  Right.

15:17.063 --> 15:18.813
He's sulking.

15:18.814 --> 15:20.274
This place looks nice.

15:25.655 --> 15:26.864
Wow.

15:27.573 --> 15:30.284
It's shattered and cracked.

15:31.702 --> 15:34.288
And there seem to be
some pieces missing. Hmm?

15:35.873 --> 15:36.874
Will it be too hard?

15:43.339 --> 15:45.215
I can make it work.

15:47.218 --> 15:48.593
It may take some time,

15:48.594 --> 15:52.013
but as long as we don't give up,
it can be fixed somehow.

15:53.349 --> 15:55.392
It would be different from the original,

15:55.393 --> 15:57.769
but let's think of it
as making it stronger.

15:57.770 --> 15:59.729
Thank you so much.

15:59.730 --> 16:01.690
Here's your coffee.

16:03.192 --> 16:06.153
My grandson must be troubling you a lot.

16:06.862 --> 16:09.739
If he does anything to irritate you,

16:09.740 --> 16:13.243
you can just smack him on the back
and kick him out.

16:13.244 --> 16:14.703
Really?

16:14.704 --> 16:18.457
He's been nagging me so much lately
that I've been thinking about it.

16:19.166 --> 16:21.501
I will keep that in mind.

16:22.670 --> 16:24.879
Stop it.

16:24.880 --> 16:28.591
You must be curious about the house.
You can take a look after you're done.

16:28.592 --> 16:31.928
No, it's your private space. I shouldn't…

16:31.929 --> 16:34.264
It's fine. It's also Chan's house.

16:34.265 --> 16:35.474
Give her a tour later.

16:36.726 --> 16:41.564
Seeing you stay with someone so nice
makes me feel at ease.

16:43.607 --> 16:45.608
Be good to him, all right?

16:45.609 --> 16:46.652
I will.

16:48.404 --> 16:51.032
Wow.

16:58.748 --> 17:02.376
So how about letting time with your dad
start moving again?

17:08.466 --> 17:09.467
Chan.

17:11.886 --> 17:13.429
It's nothing. Never mind.

17:14.180 --> 17:17.016
It was nothing.

17:20.394 --> 17:22.438
When will you visit again?

17:23.314 --> 17:25.440
That little brat isn't even seeing me off.

17:25.441 --> 17:26.608
I should give him a smack.

17:26.609 --> 17:27.818
Grandma.

17:28.694 --> 17:30.237
Can you drop me off on the way?

17:31.739 --> 17:32.823
Where?

17:33.407 --> 17:34.491
Daejeon.

17:37.912 --> 17:39.955
I don't know what I'll do there,

17:40.706 --> 17:43.084
but I think
I should at least give this back to him.

17:45.044 --> 17:46.045
Mm.

17:57.640 --> 17:59.307
I saw Yougyum this weekend.

17:59.308 --> 18:01.435
He was going to karaoke with his friends.

18:05.481 --> 18:07.191
Are you having
a lot of fun these days?

18:07.692 --> 18:09.485
Did you have fun at karaoke?

18:11.028 --> 18:12.862
What? I…

18:17.702 --> 18:19.704
Yeah, I had fun.

18:20.371 --> 18:22.248
You seemed to be having fun, too.

18:23.082 --> 18:25.668
You gave Seokhyeon
a drink with a heart on it.

18:26.377 --> 18:27.460
What?

18:28.671 --> 18:29.672
So you saw it.

18:30.089 --> 18:31.548
Yeah, I'm happy these days.

18:31.549 --> 18:33.591
I'm really glad to hear that.

18:33.592 --> 18:36.095
Yeah, so let's both live happy lives.

18:42.935 --> 18:45.688
CHEMICAL AND BIOLOGICAL ENGINEERING
PROFESSOR SUNWOO SEOK

19:03.164 --> 19:04.206
May I help you?

19:05.624 --> 19:08.209
Oh. I'm here to see Professor Sunwoo.

19:08.210 --> 19:09.627
Ah.

19:09.628 --> 19:11.296
He's gone to the president's office.

19:11.297 --> 19:13.799
May I ask what you're here for?

19:16.218 --> 19:17.553
We're family.

19:18.512 --> 19:20.806
- If he's not here--
- He'll probably be back soon.

19:21.223 --> 19:22.433
Why don't you wait inside?

19:22.725 --> 19:24.225
Ah…

19:45.664 --> 19:47.665
He's taking a while.

19:47.666 --> 19:48.834
Should I try calling him?

19:50.294 --> 19:52.338
No, I'll just go.

19:53.005 --> 19:56.675
Would it be okay
to leave this here?

19:57.218 --> 19:58.344
Sure, go ahead.

20:08.813 --> 20:11.690
KOREA SCIENCE UNIVERSITY

20:14.443 --> 20:16.277
Let me keep this, Dad.

20:44.557 --> 20:46.307
How long are you going to keep doing this?

20:46.308 --> 20:48.978
What more do I have to do
to make you stop?

21:33.981 --> 21:35.566
Excuse me, you said you're family.

21:36.150 --> 21:39.987
Are you his son who's working
as an animator in the US?

21:40.487 --> 21:41.488
You are, right?

21:42.072 --> 21:44.116
I heard a lot about you
from Professor Sunwoo.

21:44.617 --> 21:47.160
He always rushes to see
any movies that get released.

21:47.161 --> 21:49.580
He even buys tickets for his students.

22:05.679 --> 22:07.180
Can I ask you something, sir?

22:07.181 --> 22:09.892
I heard there's a famous bakery nearby.

22:10.392 --> 22:11.602
Do you know where it is?

22:13.187 --> 22:14.896
Excuse me?

22:14.897 --> 22:16.522
I came here to buy bread.

22:16.523 --> 22:19.193
I heard there's
a really famous bakery here.

22:21.362 --> 22:23.781
You're such a bad liar.

22:24.406 --> 22:27.033
Were you worried
something would've happened again?

22:27.034 --> 22:28.451
Well…

22:28.452 --> 22:30.745
I also came to check
Daejeon's fashion trends.

22:30.746 --> 22:31.829
Wow.

22:31.830 --> 22:34.083
Everyone's so fashionable here.

22:36.335 --> 22:39.837
And I thought that if anything happened,

22:39.838 --> 22:41.714
I could give you a hug.

22:41.715 --> 22:44.051
Look at you.

22:44.969 --> 22:48.222
When going to Gyeongju,
at the airport, and now Daejeon…

22:48.973 --> 22:51.350
You keep surprising me like this.

22:52.059 --> 22:54.019
You'll make me get my hopes up.

22:55.813 --> 22:58.857
I'll keep thinking you'll appear anywhere.

23:01.819 --> 23:02.820
Fine.

23:03.404 --> 23:06.699
I'll appear anywhere you are,
so you can get your hopes up.

23:09.827 --> 23:10.828
Seonu Chan!

23:34.143 --> 23:37.271
I'm so glad you've recovered.

23:38.105 --> 23:41.232
Professor Sunwoo gave up on his research
just before presenting it

23:41.233 --> 23:45.403
to go take care of you in America
when you were badly injured.

23:45.404 --> 23:46.904
We've done everything we can.

23:46.905 --> 23:49.198
Now we just have to hope
that he'll pull through.

23:49.199 --> 23:50.908
The truth is, you should be aware

23:50.909 --> 23:52.618
it's not very likely that he'll wake up.

24:16.769 --> 24:17.770
Thanks…

24:18.645 --> 24:19.855
for the watch.

24:24.568 --> 24:28.072
Maybe you should return your degree.

24:29.615 --> 24:33.035
A famous engineering professor
can't even fix a broken watch?

24:34.328 --> 24:36.830
It's working well now.

24:38.457 --> 24:39.541
Thank you…

24:40.626 --> 24:41.668
for fixing it.

24:45.964 --> 24:47.174
If you're grateful,

24:49.259 --> 24:51.845
you can pay me back later.

25:52.072 --> 25:53.991
Grandma called.

25:54.449 --> 25:56.159
She thanked me and said I did well.

25:56.160 --> 25:57.161
Really?

25:57.870 --> 25:58.912
That's great.

25:59.454 --> 26:02.456
I'm so glad you gave it back to him.

26:02.457 --> 26:05.586
That watch must be
dozens of times more precious now.

26:06.128 --> 26:08.880
It could have ended
with him being sad about losing it,

26:08.881 --> 26:12.676
but now, it's the watch that his son
fixed and returned to him.

26:23.770 --> 26:26.190
Can I see you for a moment again?

26:29.943 --> 26:30.944
Huh?

26:33.655 --> 26:35.031
How did you…

26:35.032 --> 26:38.202
Remember when we went to that restaurant?

26:38.994 --> 26:41.288
When I was in bad shape because of my ear.

26:44.082 --> 26:46.293
It's noisy in there.
I'll go bring our stuff.

26:46.752 --> 26:49.922
It must have gotten mixed up
in my stuff back then.

26:50.881 --> 26:53.175
I found it
when I unpacked my luggage here.

26:54.051 --> 26:55.052
Ah…

26:58.513 --> 27:00.807
I don't need it anymore, though.

27:06.563 --> 27:08.148
I'm already using a different one.

27:08.607 --> 27:10.900
Plus, I have dozens of pens now.

27:10.901 --> 27:13.654
Someone gave me a whole bunch
as a gift.

27:16.323 --> 27:18.241
That's why I'm giving it back now.

27:18.242 --> 27:19.284
I…

27:20.327 --> 27:22.371
was worried that I'd remind you

27:23.288 --> 27:25.582
of the memories back then.

27:26.416 --> 27:28.543
But I thought you wouldn't be wavered now.

27:30.003 --> 27:33.799
Just think of it as a pen
that's the most effective and use it.

27:35.342 --> 27:39.637
I know how important it is
to have a tool that fits you just right

27:39.638 --> 27:41.473
since I'm an animator.

27:42.641 --> 27:45.268
I can just get used to this pen.

27:48.897 --> 27:50.607
Let me borrow this for a second.

28:09.751 --> 28:11.837
Just consider this pen

28:12.546 --> 28:15.549
a pen that I found for you,
not a pen that you got as a gift

28:17.300 --> 28:20.303
or a pen that made you sad
when you lost it.

28:21.847 --> 28:25.349
And… here's a lucky charm.

28:25.350 --> 28:28.353
You know you'll get lucky
once you see an iridescent cloud.

28:29.062 --> 28:30.772
You can see one every day now,

28:31.356 --> 28:34.234
so you'll be lucky every day.

28:42.409 --> 28:43.535
Just use it.

28:46.163 --> 28:49.332
I sincerely want you to use it again.

28:53.879 --> 28:54.880
All right.

28:56.173 --> 28:57.466
I will.

29:00.135 --> 29:02.012
It's the pen you found for me now.

29:20.405 --> 29:21.615
Hello?

29:24.534 --> 29:25.535
Really?

29:26.953 --> 29:28.954
All right.

29:28.955 --> 29:30.832
Thank you. Okay.

29:34.336 --> 29:35.670
No way.

29:36.588 --> 29:38.756
- This is crazy.
- What is it?

29:38.757 --> 29:40.425
Something good really happened.

29:41.093 --> 29:42.760
I'm receiving an award.

29:42.761 --> 29:44.846
The Best Designer Award
at the Fashion Awards.

29:45.472 --> 29:47.515
See? I told you that you'd be lucky.

29:47.516 --> 29:49.726
Congratulations.

30:04.699 --> 30:06.076
Genius.

30:07.577 --> 30:09.036
Are you here?

30:09.037 --> 30:10.038
Huh?

30:11.206 --> 30:12.207
Hey, Genius.

30:15.418 --> 30:16.628
Is there something there?

30:18.755 --> 30:20.173
What…

30:21.007 --> 30:22.091
Nabong!

30:23.385 --> 30:25.511
What are you doing here at this hour?

30:25.512 --> 30:26.596
Hey, Manjae.

30:27.097 --> 30:30.766
I wanted to get a cup of coffee
after I finished work,

30:30.767 --> 30:32.435
but I didn't realize it was so late.

30:34.146 --> 30:37.356
The snow was beautiful,
so I was watching it for a bit.

30:37.357 --> 30:39.066
It's so late…

30:39.067 --> 30:40.986
And you're dressed so lightly.

30:41.444 --> 30:42.528
It's cold.

30:42.529 --> 30:43.780
Come on, let's go inside.

30:46.032 --> 30:47.367
Get yourself warmed up.

30:49.953 --> 30:52.329
What on earth is going on?

30:52.330 --> 30:55.250
I was so absorbed in work,
I didn't notice the time.

30:55.876 --> 30:58.044
You know how focused I can get.

31:02.507 --> 31:03.925
Are you sure nothing's wrong?

31:07.429 --> 31:08.888
Is everything really okay?

31:08.889 --> 31:10.891
Is this some trending challenge?

31:11.391 --> 31:13.894
Why is everyone asking me that?

31:15.061 --> 31:18.273
Did I neglect my skincare
because I was too busy?

31:27.699 --> 31:30.160
Have some warm tea.

31:48.428 --> 31:49.679
What on earth

31:50.472 --> 31:52.724
is going on with you?

32:07.364 --> 32:09.491
LAUNDRY DETERGENT
LAVENDER

32:11.576 --> 32:13.452
Aren't you my Hadam?

32:17.040 --> 32:18.208
It's me.

32:19.459 --> 32:21.127
Mom.

32:22.420 --> 32:23.755
Mom?

32:24.923 --> 32:26.215
Oh, my goodness!

32:26.216 --> 32:28.425
I finally got to meet you.

32:28.426 --> 32:30.219
I wanted to see you so much.

32:30.220 --> 32:33.013
It's me, Yougyum's mom.

32:33.014 --> 32:34.683
What? Ah…

32:35.809 --> 32:36.810
Ah!

32:37.644 --> 32:38.894
Hello.

32:38.895 --> 32:41.105
Goodness, it's so nice to meet you.

32:41.106 --> 32:42.940
I recognized you right away.

32:42.941 --> 32:46.026
Our house is plastered with photos of you.

32:46.027 --> 32:49.071
I feel like I'm meeting a celebrity.

32:49.072 --> 32:52.993
If it's all right, could I give you a hug?

32:57.414 --> 33:00.374
My dear Hadam.

33:00.375 --> 33:03.669
It's so nice to see you.

33:11.594 --> 33:14.014
What's wrong? What is it?

33:14.848 --> 33:20.060
♪ Sleep well, dear Hadam ♪

33:20.061 --> 33:24.398
♪ Sleep in Mommy's arms ♪

33:24.399 --> 33:29.404
♪ Sleep well, dear Hadam ♪

33:29.904 --> 33:34.283
♪ Sleep tight ♪

33:34.284 --> 33:35.452
I found…

33:39.622 --> 33:40.915
Mom's smell.

33:55.889 --> 33:58.183
Come on. I'll make you a meal.

33:59.351 --> 34:01.853
Let's go.

34:02.645 --> 34:04.188
Excuse me.

34:04.189 --> 34:05.814
Where is the grocery store?

34:07.108 --> 34:08.567
Excuse me.

34:08.568 --> 34:10.194
Where is the grocery store?

34:10.195 --> 34:12.946
-  Honey.
- Come on in.

34:16.159 --> 34:17.410
Hello.

34:18.036 --> 34:19.370
Look who it is!

34:19.371 --> 34:21.038
Isn't she our superstar?

34:21.039 --> 34:22.915
- Our dear Hadam.
- Ah…

34:22.916 --> 34:24.625
We told Yougyum to bring you,

34:24.626 --> 34:26.835
but he said
we shouldn't bother your studies

34:26.836 --> 34:29.505
and kept you hidden all along.

34:29.506 --> 34:31.423
I ran into her by chance
at the supermarket.

34:31.424 --> 34:33.175
Welcome.

34:33.176 --> 34:34.343
Did you eat?

34:34.344 --> 34:35.594
Join us for a meal.

34:36.805 --> 34:40.391
Gosh. I told you to bring me
when you're buying heavy stuff.

34:40.392 --> 34:42.684
I'll bring these upstairs.

34:42.685 --> 34:44.019
Gosh!

34:44.020 --> 34:45.355
My goodness.

34:49.317 --> 34:52.529
I can't believe him.

34:57.450 --> 34:59.661
LET'S BE SOMEONE HADAM WILL BE PROUD OF!

35:00.537 --> 35:02.914
I wondered why
he only got perfect scores in English.

35:03.373 --> 35:05.666
I heard you told him in your first year.

35:05.667 --> 35:07.334
The Major League?

35:07.335 --> 35:08.961
If that's your goal,

35:08.962 --> 35:11.922
shouldn't you at least
study English in advance?

35:11.923 --> 35:14.467
I want to be better
than I was yesterday.

35:14.801 --> 35:15.802
"Challenge."

35:16.136 --> 35:17.219
Challenge.

35:17.220 --> 35:20.347
Since then,
his father has been studying English, too.

35:20.348 --> 35:22.433
He said he wants to help Yougyum.

35:22.434 --> 35:25.185
This is how much influence
you have over our family.

35:27.605 --> 35:29.189
He's unbelievable.

35:29.190 --> 35:31.859
Honey, should I braise the fish?

35:31.860 --> 35:33.110
Hang on.

35:33.111 --> 35:34.821
- Sorry. Take a look around.
- Okay.

35:39.451 --> 35:43.203
But how did you end up dating Yougyum?

35:43.204 --> 35:46.248
He said he had a crush on you
since elementary school.

35:46.249 --> 35:48.710
Thinking back,

35:49.210 --> 35:51.754
he was the only one who understood me.

35:53.673 --> 35:56.049
Why aren't your parents
here for the field day?

35:56.050 --> 35:59.636
Hey, she's the poor kid
whose parents both died.

35:59.637 --> 36:01.221
Really? That's so pitiful.

36:01.222 --> 36:05.267
Hey, having your parents
pass away isn't pitiful.

36:05.268 --> 36:06.478
It's just sad.

36:10.190 --> 36:13.025
I solved this when I stayed up
studying last night.

36:13.026 --> 36:14.319
Hadam.

36:15.069 --> 36:18.405
In baseball, throwing pull power
every time will strain your body.

36:18.406 --> 36:20.699
You need a breather to grow stronger.

36:20.700 --> 36:22.243
A breather?

36:23.578 --> 36:24.579
That's why…

36:27.457 --> 36:28.583
you need a breather now.

36:30.376 --> 36:32.629
All right. Pitcher Cha Yougyum
is ready to throw.

36:38.510 --> 36:39.635
I hit it!

36:39.636 --> 36:41.012
Run, Hadam!

36:42.347 --> 36:43.722
Go!

36:48.978 --> 36:50.063
Right.

36:53.650 --> 36:57.070
Yougyum always understood me.

37:04.702 --> 37:07.455
Nabong, guess what I found?

37:16.756 --> 37:19.716
Manjae, where did you get that photo?

37:19.717 --> 37:20.843
Oh.

37:20.844 --> 37:22.845
I was organizing my vinyl collection,

37:22.846 --> 37:25.806
and it just fell out.

37:25.807 --> 37:28.976
I can't believe it.
That was such a long time ago.

37:28.977 --> 37:30.562
I wonder if that tree is still there.

37:31.521 --> 37:36.276
Remember the tteokbokki place
we used to go to in the market?

37:36.693 --> 37:37.860
What was it called?

37:37.861 --> 37:40.070
- Ah! Fat Tteokbokki.
- Fat Tteokbokki.

37:40.071 --> 37:41.947
Right?

37:43.449 --> 37:46.536
Ah… I'm craving
that super sweet tteokbokki.

37:47.287 --> 37:50.290
Do you want to go
have tteokbokki this evening?

37:51.958 --> 37:53.542
No…

37:53.543 --> 37:56.003
You shouldn't ditch work, right?

37:56.004 --> 37:57.629
Come on.

37:57.630 --> 38:00.884
Nabong, have you forgotten
that I'm the owner?

38:01.926 --> 38:03.802
I can totally ditch work.

38:05.680 --> 38:06.805
Well, well.

38:06.806 --> 38:09.391
I caught you. Are you ditching work?

38:09.392 --> 38:11.143
No, I'm receiving an award.

38:11.144 --> 38:13.478
Oh, right. The Fashion Awards is today.

38:13.479 --> 38:15.355
Congratulations.

38:15.356 --> 38:16.649
See you.

38:24.824 --> 38:26.366
Love.

38:26.367 --> 38:29.286
That means you like him too.

38:29.287 --> 38:31.163
No way.

38:31.164 --> 38:32.247
Was he right?

38:32.248 --> 38:35.542
Why does he look so cool
when he's just walking?

38:40.673 --> 38:42.424
Why am I blushing?

38:42.425 --> 38:43.968
And why am I sweating?

38:51.184 --> 38:53.518
Are you free this evening?

38:53.519 --> 38:56.022
This evening?
Not morning or afternoon?

38:56.648 --> 38:59.149
Is he asking me out?

38:59.150 --> 39:01.109
On a date?

39:01.110 --> 39:03.278
I got a reply that the factory

39:03.279 --> 39:05.822
couldn't get any of the bio silk
you talked about.

39:05.823 --> 39:07.115
I did more research

39:07.116 --> 39:10.786
and got in touch with an industry
tech reporter who wrote about it.

39:10.787 --> 39:12.663
We're meeting this evening.

39:12.664 --> 39:14.998
We may find a way to do it.

39:14.999 --> 39:18.252
Mr. Yeon's cheeks
seem a little red, too.

39:18.753 --> 39:21.046
Huh? And he's sweating.

39:21.047 --> 39:22.381
Was Raemee really right?

39:22.382 --> 39:25.343
Then we really like each other?

39:28.388 --> 39:31.099
Great job with the meeting.

39:34.811 --> 39:36.311
How about some wine?

39:36.312 --> 39:37.647
Just you and me,

39:38.231 --> 39:39.273
alone.

39:40.108 --> 39:42.151
Sure. I'd like that.

39:42.735 --> 39:44.362
Pardon? Uh…

39:44.988 --> 39:47.198
Are you saying you'll come?

39:49.033 --> 39:50.367
Ah.

39:50.368 --> 39:52.411
Yes, I'm free.

39:52.412 --> 39:54.413
I'll drive, then.

39:54.414 --> 39:56.624
I'll see you at the parking lot
at 7:00 p.m.

40:03.798 --> 40:06.092
Why are we meeting at 7:00 p.m.?

40:07.760 --> 40:09.261
Right.

40:09.262 --> 40:10.304
The new material.

40:11.639 --> 40:12.723
The meeting.

40:12.724 --> 40:14.141
GYUM'S LAUNDRY

40:14.142 --> 40:15.685
I'm home.

40:18.771 --> 40:20.063
Mom.

40:20.064 --> 40:22.399
Mom, I must have lost my mind.

40:22.400 --> 40:25.862
I miss Hadam so much,
I must be hallucinating.

40:27.572 --> 40:29.573
But…

40:29.574 --> 40:32.451
it's still so nice to see her.

40:37.999 --> 40:39.167
You idiot.

40:40.084 --> 40:41.335
It's really me.

40:41.961 --> 40:43.420
Wow.

40:43.421 --> 40:44.589
She's even talking now.

40:45.339 --> 40:49.051
I must have gone crazy
from missing her so much.

40:49.052 --> 40:50.470
You idiot.

40:51.888 --> 40:53.556
It really is me.

40:55.058 --> 40:58.310
Is it really you?

40:58.311 --> 41:00.312
You're really Hadam?

41:00.313 --> 41:02.898
I didn't give Seokhyeon my number.

41:02.899 --> 41:06.777
Someone left a drink at my seat
with a heart post-it,

41:06.778 --> 41:09.113
and I rushed out thinking it was from you.

41:09.572 --> 41:12.116
When I heard it was from Seokhyeon,
I gave it back to him.

41:16.329 --> 41:17.330
Really?

41:17.955 --> 41:19.248
I'm sorry I misunderstood.

41:19.832 --> 41:21.792
I wasn't having fun at karaoke either.

41:21.793 --> 41:24.045
My friends took me there to comfort me,

41:24.629 --> 41:26.797
but I just kept crying
at the thought of you.

41:26.798 --> 41:28.883
I'm sorry I misunderstood you, too.

41:29.967 --> 41:32.595
But why are you wearing glasses?

41:33.096 --> 41:34.472
Has your eyesight gotten bad?

41:35.014 --> 41:36.015
No,

41:37.391 --> 41:38.767
I don't need them now.

41:38.768 --> 41:41.562
And you? Why were you
at the nurse's office? Were you sick?

41:44.273 --> 41:46.025
I just got a small cut on my hand,

41:46.776 --> 41:48.402
but I'm all better now.

41:57.120 --> 41:58.787
I'm sorry, Hadam.

41:58.788 --> 42:01.164
I'm more sorry.

42:01.165 --> 42:02.999
I missed you so much.

42:03.000 --> 42:05.836
I missed you even more.

42:05.837 --> 42:08.922
The Best Designer Award.

42:08.923 --> 42:11.383
Nana Atelier, Song Haran.

42:11.384 --> 42:13.343
There are two winners this year.

42:13.344 --> 42:15.804
Onne Apparel, Kang Eunchan.

42:27.733 --> 42:28.734
Haran.

42:29.193 --> 42:31.820
I have to go to the factory.
There's a fabric issue.

42:31.821 --> 42:34.323
I booked a table at Haeon,
the restaurant nearby.

42:35.575 --> 42:36.700
Take this and go there.

42:36.701 --> 42:40.453
I said I'd buy dinner for my brother,
but I can't let him eat alone.

42:40.454 --> 42:42.874
Sorry, but just have dinner
with him, okay?

42:44.250 --> 42:46.960
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

42:46.961 --> 42:49.045
♪ Happy birthday… ♪

42:51.090 --> 42:54.467
I'm sorry. I haven't slept
for the past three days.

42:54.468 --> 42:56.469
Sorry. Right.

42:56.470 --> 42:58.096
♪ Happy birthday, dear… ♪

42:58.097 --> 42:59.598
Kang Hyeokchan.

42:59.599 --> 43:01.558
♪ Kang Hyeokchan ♪

43:01.559 --> 43:03.435
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

43:08.274 --> 43:10.902
A Mr. Kang from our house
asked me to give it to you.

43:11.360 --> 43:12.904
- What?
- Good luck.

43:13.571 --> 43:15.030
VITAMINS FOR ENERGY
A CUSHION FOR A NAP

43:15.031 --> 43:16.615
CHOCOLATE AFTER LUNCH
CHAMOMILE AFTER WORK

43:16.616 --> 43:17.658
WITH THESE, YOU CAN SLEEP BETTER

43:26.125 --> 43:27.335
- I love you.
- Hmm?

43:28.336 --> 43:29.420
That's so sudden.

43:35.426 --> 43:36.427
It's work.

43:37.511 --> 43:39.305
Good luck with the embassy interview.

43:42.683 --> 43:43.726
Hello?

43:44.060 --> 43:47.312
I can't believe I have to work
when you're leaving.

43:47.313 --> 43:48.648
I'm so sorry, Chan.

43:49.357 --> 43:50.690
It's fine.

43:50.691 --> 43:53.026
I told you I won't get upset
about you being busy.

43:53.027 --> 43:55.195
I'll be back during vacation. I love you.

43:55.196 --> 43:56.529
I'm so sorry.

43:56.530 --> 43:58.199
Leave me a message when you arrive.

43:59.575 --> 44:03.119
I can't go back to Korea
because of my lab schedule.

44:03.120 --> 44:06.040
And my phone's broken,
so I won't be able to text for a while.

44:06.707 --> 44:08.875
Leave me a message
if there's anything urgent.

44:08.876 --> 44:10.544
I knew it.

44:11.003 --> 44:12.922
Are you sure he just doesn't want to come?

44:13.422 --> 44:15.924
- What?
- Well, I haven't seen it myself,

44:15.925 --> 44:18.635
but he was so nice to you
when he was in Seoul.

44:18.636 --> 44:21.429
But you were always busy
and didn't keep in touch often.

44:21.430 --> 44:23.139
You didn't even show much affection.

44:23.140 --> 44:24.849
You'll get dumped at this rate.

44:24.850 --> 44:27.520
You're right.
I guess I deserve it.

44:28.521 --> 44:29.813
That's too bad.

44:29.814 --> 44:31.982
What's that reaction?

44:31.983 --> 44:33.984
Do you even like Hyeokchan?

44:33.985 --> 44:36.611
Of course I do. He's my boyfriend.

44:36.612 --> 44:38.322
No, not like that.

44:38.906 --> 44:40.157
Do you love him?

44:40.783 --> 44:41.784
Mmm?

44:42.326 --> 44:43.743
Did Chan send that?

44:43.744 --> 44:45.997
He sent a drawing pen
for his designer girlfriend?

44:47.081 --> 44:49.917
Wow. And even with your name
engraved on it?

44:52.044 --> 44:55.046
But how did you come up
with the idea of sending me a pen?

44:56.465 --> 44:58.925
I KEPT THINKING ABOUT HOW YOU SAID
YOU FELT LIKE YOU WERE TRAPPED

44:58.926 --> 45:00.969
I GUESS I WANTED THAT PEN
TO BE THAT "IF" FOR YOU

45:02.596 --> 45:05.266
Chan understands me so well…

45:05.933 --> 45:06.934
SORRY, I WAS RAMBLING

45:07.893 --> 45:11.522
I miss you, Hyeokchan.

45:12.857 --> 45:15.609
Ta-da! I'm at the airport!

45:15.735 --> 45:17.820
I wanted to tell you something in person.

45:18.195 --> 45:20.323
Chan. I love you.

45:21.824 --> 45:23.992
I love you, Chan.

45:23.993 --> 45:25.452
Haran, what do I do?

45:25.453 --> 45:26.454
Chan…

45:26.954 --> 45:29.582
Hyeokchan is dead.

45:42.428 --> 45:44.221
I moved to Onne Apparel.

45:45.431 --> 45:48.893
It's awkward giving you my business card.

45:52.313 --> 45:54.231
Have you been well?

45:56.692 --> 45:57.860
It's already been…

45:58.986 --> 45:59.987
seven years.

46:01.322 --> 46:04.075
I always wondered how you were doing,

46:04.617 --> 46:06.285
but I felt too guilty to contact you.

46:07.036 --> 46:09.830
Why would you feel guilty?

46:18.172 --> 46:20.049
- What is it?
- Oh…

46:21.425 --> 46:24.719
Were you getting checkups here?

46:24.720 --> 46:25.721
Huh?

46:26.639 --> 46:28.473
Ahh.

46:28.474 --> 46:31.851
I was at a different ER
when I collapsed last time.

46:33.229 --> 46:35.814
I got a referral, so I come here.

46:35.815 --> 46:37.065
It's closer.

46:37.066 --> 46:38.401
- What is it?
- Ah…

46:39.110 --> 46:42.655
I got treated here before.

46:43.614 --> 46:46.534
I'll go ask where we can get the results.

46:52.665 --> 46:54.208
We have to go to the annex.

46:54.834 --> 46:55.918
Really?

46:56.877 --> 46:59.130
But why are you dressed up today?

47:00.297 --> 47:01.589
Hmm?

47:01.590 --> 47:04.885
I have to be dressed up
to go somewhere later.

47:05.469 --> 47:07.470
Mmm…

47:07.471 --> 47:08.639
Where are you going?

47:14.145 --> 47:15.228
The door is closing.

47:15.229 --> 47:17.565
The door is closing.

47:34.165 --> 47:36.959
Huh? Hey, roomie!

47:57.938 --> 47:58.939
Mr. Park.

48:00.274 --> 48:02.943
Sorry, I'll head over there.

48:05.488 --> 48:06.489
Okay.

48:12.786 --> 48:15.663
Visiting neurology resident
from Boston General Hospital,

48:15.664 --> 48:16.832
Cha Sujin.

48:17.374 --> 48:18.666
I'm Cha Sujin.

48:18.667 --> 48:20.835
I'll do my best
to learn as much as I can here.

48:20.836 --> 48:22.630
Nice to meet you all.

48:27.635 --> 48:28.885
Dr. Cha.

48:28.886 --> 48:30.470
You shouldn't wear accessories here.

48:30.471 --> 48:33.724
Sorry. I forgot to take it off.

48:35.226 --> 48:37.685
MEDICAL STAFF SEARCH

48:37.686 --> 48:40.564
LEE SUJIN

48:41.732 --> 48:43.526
I'm sure she was in a gown.

48:51.617 --> 48:52.618
All right.

48:53.244 --> 48:55.036
I got the results.

48:55.037 --> 48:58.374
But why did you suddenly get off earlier?

48:59.083 --> 49:01.084
Oh. It was nothing.

49:01.085 --> 49:02.794
There's a convenience store nearby.

49:02.795 --> 49:04.546
I'll go buy some drinks for the nurses.

49:04.547 --> 49:06.048
Mmm.

49:07.007 --> 49:09.176
Hmm? They didn't say it was going to rain.

49:09.635 --> 49:10.802
Is it a shower?

49:10.803 --> 49:13.096
I have a hood, so it's fine.
I'll be back soon.

49:13.097 --> 49:14.431
Okay.

49:20.020 --> 49:22.146
Who's that? Your friend?

49:22.147 --> 49:23.816
No, just my roommate.

49:27.278 --> 49:30.030
Dr. Cha, we're starting rounds.

49:30.656 --> 49:31.657
Okay.

49:34.827 --> 49:35.911
Hospitalized?

49:36.620 --> 49:38.747
- Hyeokchan?
-  Don't you remember?

49:39.331 --> 49:41.833
He hurt his hand badly in the lab.

49:41.834 --> 49:43.085
He even got surgery.

49:44.044 --> 49:45.129
A surgery?

49:45.921 --> 49:48.548
I never heard anything about that.

49:51.552 --> 49:52.969
Manjae, what do you think?

49:52.970 --> 49:55.972
It looks like
Genius' paw print. It's cute.

49:55.973 --> 49:57.515
- Right?
- Should I buy it for you?

49:57.516 --> 49:59.642
- Sure.
- Okay. How much is it?

49:59.643 --> 50:01.019
- Manjae!
- What? What is it?

50:01.020 --> 50:02.312
Tteokbokki! Tteokbokki!

50:08.652 --> 50:10.487
It's good.

50:11.113 --> 50:14.324
Having tteokbokki after ditching
is the best.

50:14.325 --> 50:15.408
Right?

50:15.409 --> 50:18.161
That only applies
to the Chuncheon fashionista Nabong.

50:18.162 --> 50:20.289
I never ditched school.

50:20.914 --> 50:23.708
Ah. Right, of course.

50:23.709 --> 50:27.045
You were the bookworm Park Manjae.

50:27.046 --> 50:28.796
That's right.

50:30.382 --> 50:31.425
Excuse me.

50:31.967 --> 50:34.510
Are you Kim Nana, by any chance?

50:34.511 --> 50:35.803
It seems like it, right?

50:35.804 --> 50:37.722
We're fashion design majors,

50:37.723 --> 50:40.058
and we're huge fans.

50:40.059 --> 50:42.018
Could I have an autograph?

50:42.019 --> 50:45.396
Mmm… Oh, dear. My face is my autograph.

50:45.397 --> 50:47.774
You can take a selfie with me.

50:47.775 --> 50:50.277
One, two, three.

50:51.028 --> 50:53.237
Thank you.

50:53.238 --> 50:56.324
By the way, your husband is freaking…

50:56.325 --> 50:58.242
I mean, he's really cool.

50:58.243 --> 51:00.162
- No, I'm…
- He's freaking cool, isn't he?

51:00.788 --> 51:03.122
I care about looks.

51:13.133 --> 51:15.510
Why do I feel so nervous
being alone with him?

51:15.511 --> 51:17.345
Oh… I feel so hot.

51:17.346 --> 51:20.473
Should I turn off the heater?
Would it show that I'm nervous?

51:20.474 --> 51:22.809
It's hot.

51:29.525 --> 51:30.609
Should I close the window?

51:31.235 --> 51:33.070
No, it's fine. You can do as you like.

51:42.413 --> 51:45.039
Then would it be possible to get samples?

51:45.040 --> 51:48.459
Yes, but it's over five times
the price of silk,

51:48.460 --> 51:50.461
and the durability tests
aren't stable yet.

51:50.462 --> 51:52.673
That's why I want to try this.

51:53.215 --> 51:54.465
I want to make clothes

51:54.466 --> 51:56.635
not just for display
but to prove the future.

51:57.094 --> 51:59.846
I really want to achieve that
for our brand.

51:59.847 --> 52:01.723
You seem very determined.

52:01.724 --> 52:04.058
How should we get the samples?

52:04.059 --> 52:06.394
There's a research facility
I came in touch with.

52:06.395 --> 52:09.022
It's a bio startup company.
I'll give you their number.

52:09.565 --> 52:10.858
- Really?
-  Yes.

52:11.358 --> 52:15.236
And I'll ask them again
for their cooperation.

52:15.237 --> 52:17.196
Thank you…

52:17.197 --> 52:18.406
I was just so grateful.

52:18.407 --> 52:20.825
- Are you all right?
-  Yes.

52:20.826 --> 52:22.827
- You really mean it?
- Of course.

52:22.828 --> 52:24.912
- Ms. Song, here's my business card.
- Ah.

52:24.913 --> 52:26.706
Contact me if you have any questions.

52:26.707 --> 52:27.915
Thank you.

52:27.916 --> 52:29.542
It was nice seeing you again, Taeseok.

52:29.543 --> 52:32.545
What? Do you two know each other?

52:32.546 --> 52:33.881
Why didn't you tell me?

52:34.465 --> 52:37.550
I'm actually his junior from college.

52:37.551 --> 52:38.760
He asked me

52:38.761 --> 52:40.721
to keep it a secret
in case you felt uneasy.

52:41.555 --> 52:44.600
I tried to get close to him,
but he never let me back then.

52:45.058 --> 52:46.184
And now--

52:46.185 --> 52:48.269
Thank you for today, Mr. Chae.

52:48.270 --> 52:49.521
I'll see you next time.

52:50.063 --> 52:51.273
You haven't changed a bit.

52:53.275 --> 52:56.736
I'd like to get to know you better.

52:56.737 --> 52:58.947
How about a glass of wine together?

52:59.573 --> 53:00.949
Just the two of us.

53:01.450 --> 53:04.661
Just the two of us?

53:05.245 --> 53:06.246
That's okay, right?

53:07.080 --> 53:09.249
I don't think it's my place
to say yes or no.

53:10.167 --> 53:11.168
Then excuse me.

53:14.046 --> 53:15.671
What was that?

53:15.672 --> 53:17.716
Did he just set me up on a date?

53:18.133 --> 53:19.718
Didn't he have feelings for me?

53:21.011 --> 53:22.095
Mr. Yeon.

53:22.638 --> 53:25.682
Is it really okay for me
to have a drink with him, alone?

53:26.308 --> 53:28.309
Why are you asking me that?

53:28.310 --> 53:30.353
I think it's your business.

53:31.772 --> 53:33.524
Ah. Fine.

53:37.402 --> 53:40.112
Mr. Chae, let's go have some wine.

53:40.113 --> 53:41.865
I'm really craving a drink today.

53:51.583 --> 53:53.918
Hadam, enjoy these dishes.

53:53.919 --> 53:56.671
You even packed side dishes for me?

53:56.672 --> 53:57.922
Thank you.

53:57.923 --> 53:59.882
Make sure to visit after the CSAT.

53:59.883 --> 54:01.343
I promise I will.

54:02.386 --> 54:05.180
But could you give me

54:06.682 --> 54:08.099
one more hug?

54:08.100 --> 54:10.434
Of course, I can. Come here.

54:13.063 --> 54:15.022
I'll see you again later. Hmm?

54:15.023 --> 54:16.148
Okay.

54:16.149 --> 54:18.693
- Me too. I want a hug, too.
- My goodness!

54:18.694 --> 54:21.237
Then I should join as well.

54:25.826 --> 54:29.412
A surgery?
I never heard anything about that.

54:29.413 --> 54:30.873
You didn't know?

54:31.540 --> 54:34.835
I guess Chan didn't tell you
in case you got worried.

54:39.423 --> 54:41.883
Excuse me.

54:41.884 --> 54:46.221
You're Designer Song Haran
who won the Best Designer Award, right?

54:47.055 --> 54:49.307
Oh? How are you here?

54:49.308 --> 54:52.227
I have a habit of congratulating people
who receive awards.

54:53.103 --> 54:54.396
Here.

54:54.896 --> 54:55.980
Congratulations.

54:58.525 --> 54:59.568
Thanks.

55:00.652 --> 55:03.739
But why do you look so down

55:04.323 --> 55:05.699
when you just won an award?

55:06.366 --> 55:08.451
No, I'm really happy.

55:08.452 --> 55:10.579
No, your expression looks…

55:12.080 --> 55:13.832
like this.

55:14.541 --> 55:17.043
Let's go.

55:17.044 --> 55:18.211
Go where?

55:19.004 --> 55:20.797
Photos? That's so random.

55:21.632 --> 55:23.424
I told you, what you took doesn't count.

55:23.425 --> 55:25.051
Oh. This one's good.

55:25.052 --> 55:26.386
All right. Come here.

55:30.098 --> 55:32.267
Our Best Designer.

55:34.603 --> 55:37.022
Okay. One, two, three.

55:39.524 --> 55:40.692
You should smile.

55:41.526 --> 55:42.860
This time with the flowers.

55:42.861 --> 55:43.862
Here. Smile.

55:45.447 --> 55:47.491
All right. One, two, three.

55:48.408 --> 55:51.285
I'll do an ugly face for you
to make you look prettier.

55:51.286 --> 55:53.246
One, two, three.

55:57.459 --> 55:59.169
Pretty pose.

56:00.545 --> 56:02.589
Look at your expressions.

56:05.258 --> 56:07.259
- Let's go to our next course.
- What?

56:07.260 --> 56:09.346
Where? Where are we going?

56:10.806 --> 56:12.474
Come on, let's go.

56:13.266 --> 56:14.267
This way.

56:17.521 --> 56:20.649
Wow. You came to such
a nice place alone? Tsk.

56:21.191 --> 56:23.276
You're the one
who disappeared without telling me.

56:25.737 --> 56:28.114
Excuse me, could you take a picture of us?

56:28.115 --> 56:29.949
Sure, of course.

56:29.950 --> 56:31.827
Two, three.

56:32.411 --> 56:34.453
- Thank you.
-  Thank you.

56:34.454 --> 56:36.415
Would you like a photo, too?

56:37.624 --> 56:38.958
Sure.

56:38.959 --> 56:41.502
Okay. Smile.

56:41.503 --> 56:43.546
It'll look nice
if you smile at each other.

56:43.547 --> 56:45.590
- Can you look at each other?
- Like this?

56:49.720 --> 56:51.304
What should I do?

56:52.180 --> 56:54.598
I'll do an ugly face for you.

56:54.599 --> 56:56.768
- We'll take one for you, too.
- Oh, I'm okay.

57:02.023 --> 57:03.233
Thank you.

57:05.819 --> 57:07.278
I'll take it now.

57:07.279 --> 57:09.197
One, two, three.

57:15.579 --> 57:18.832
There's a blanket I've been using
since I was a baby,

57:19.750 --> 57:21.793
and it had this distinctive scent.

57:23.628 --> 57:27.132
It felt warm and comforting

57:28.884 --> 57:31.052
and made me feel like I'm going to cry.

57:33.638 --> 57:35.766
But that scent disappeared.

57:36.433 --> 57:38.643
It smelled just like my mom used to.

57:40.520 --> 57:42.439
But when your mom hugged me earlier,

57:44.858 --> 57:46.108
I smelled the same scent.

57:53.366 --> 57:54.576
So I ended up crying.

57:56.244 --> 57:58.330
I thought it was the smell of detergent,

57:59.539 --> 58:01.208
but I guess that was the scent of a mom.

58:04.044 --> 58:06.546
Oh? Then wouldn't I smell similar?

58:07.839 --> 58:08.840
Try smelling me.

58:14.346 --> 58:16.431
You have a different scent.

58:18.183 --> 58:20.768
I'm going to marry you, no matter what.

58:20.769 --> 58:21.894
What?

58:21.895 --> 58:24.146
Whenever I see you,

58:24.147 --> 58:27.191
I wonder how you could be so wonderful.

58:27.192 --> 58:29.194
But I understood when I saw your parents.

58:29.778 --> 58:32.072
If they become my family,

58:32.656 --> 58:34.282
I'll be so happy.

58:36.326 --> 58:38.119
Still, I'll love you the most.

58:39.704 --> 58:40.747
What do I do?

58:41.373 --> 58:44.917
I'm so happy,
I feel like I'm going to faint.

58:44.918 --> 58:48.212
There's nothing left
but happiness for us.

58:48.213 --> 58:49.339
Mm.

58:50.507 --> 58:52.800
Let's go. I want to study.

58:52.801 --> 58:54.052
Okay.

58:55.178 --> 58:56.513
The minimum CSAT requirement?

58:57.222 --> 58:59.182
It's going to be a piece of cake.

59:02.769 --> 59:04.144
Why aren't you coming?

59:05.856 --> 59:07.482
Did you really faint?

59:08.567 --> 59:11.027
Come on. Stop fooling around.

59:12.696 --> 59:15.073
Hadam, what do I do?

59:18.285 --> 59:20.579
I can't get up.

59:21.162 --> 59:22.246
My foot…

59:22.247 --> 59:23.330
What?

59:27.669 --> 59:29.421
Huh?

59:37.053 --> 59:38.137
Yougyum…

59:39.723 --> 59:41.307
Thank you for the umbrella.

59:44.227 --> 59:45.687
See you.

59:46.396 --> 59:47.605
-  Yes!
-  Bye.

59:47.606 --> 59:48.772
Sure. Bye.

59:48.773 --> 59:50.065
- Bye.
- Get home safely.

59:50.066 --> 59:51.067
Okay.

59:52.611 --> 59:56.364
Tsk. He made me
get my hopes up for nothing.

59:58.658 --> 01:00:00.911
I should thank him.

01:00:01.494 --> 01:00:05.040
I'm so grateful that he introduced us.

01:00:10.086 --> 01:00:11.212
Why isn't he picking up?

01:00:16.801 --> 01:00:20.972
Mr. Yeon, I had so much fun
with Mr. Chae today…

01:00:22.641 --> 01:00:23.933
What are you spying on?

01:00:23.934 --> 01:00:25.685
Gosh, you scared me.

01:00:26.686 --> 01:00:29.772
Did Mr. Yeon not come back here
after the meeting?

01:00:29.773 --> 01:00:31.566
He just dropped by for a bit and left.

01:00:32.233 --> 01:00:33.317
Ah.

01:00:33.318 --> 01:00:34.486
You'd better buy me lunch…

01:00:34.945 --> 01:00:37.489
for the information.

01:00:38.949 --> 01:00:41.200
He always gets off work late, though.

01:00:41.201 --> 01:00:42.410
Mr. Yeon Taeseok?

01:00:43.620 --> 01:00:44.996
There's a delivery for you.

01:00:45.664 --> 01:00:47.414
I'll take that.

01:00:47.415 --> 01:00:49.041
Thank you.

01:00:49.042 --> 01:00:51.127
YEON TAESEOK

01:00:57.968 --> 01:00:59.636
Mr. Yeon.

01:01:04.516 --> 01:01:06.601
What? He's not home, either?

01:01:11.022 --> 01:01:12.857
Mr. Yeon, I…

01:01:14.109 --> 01:01:15.192
Oh?

01:01:17.529 --> 01:01:18.821
What…

01:01:18.822 --> 01:01:20.407
What's going on?

01:01:24.035 --> 01:01:27.872
This keychain is so cute.

01:01:28.373 --> 01:01:31.084
Manjae, let's go have sujebi next time.

01:01:32.502 --> 01:01:35.629
And let's visit Chuncheon as well
before it gets colder.

01:01:35.630 --> 01:01:37.090
- Let's…
- Kim Nabong.

01:01:38.425 --> 01:01:39.550
What?

01:01:39.551 --> 01:01:40.552
Why aren't you coming?

01:01:41.886 --> 01:01:42.971
You.

01:01:45.306 --> 01:01:46.683
Where are you going this time?

01:01:47.308 --> 01:01:48.726
I said let's go to Chuncheon.

01:01:48.727 --> 01:01:51.145
You're behaving just like back then.

01:01:51.146 --> 01:01:54.023
When you suddenly left for France
when you were 20,

01:01:54.024 --> 01:01:55.315
you acted just like this.

01:01:55.316 --> 01:01:57.943
You called me out of the blue

01:01:57.944 --> 01:02:00.321
and said, "Let's do this. Let's go here."

01:02:01.072 --> 01:02:04.033
Then you suddenly disappeared
without saying anything.

01:02:07.037 --> 01:02:09.955
That was a long time ago. Don't be silly.

01:02:09.956 --> 01:02:10.999
Tell me.

01:02:11.833 --> 01:02:13.126
What is it this time?

01:02:13.585 --> 01:02:15.336
What on earth is going on with you?

01:02:30.769 --> 01:02:31.895
Hello?

01:02:33.605 --> 01:02:35.732
Yes. May I ask who's calling?

01:02:44.741 --> 01:02:45.991
Oh…

01:02:45.992 --> 01:02:47.326
All right.

01:02:47.327 --> 01:02:48.828
I'll go and check.

01:02:58.755 --> 01:03:00.799
Ah.

01:03:06.846 --> 01:03:09.808
I miss you already.

01:03:14.479 --> 01:03:16.606
- Hmm?
-  Can you come out for a bit?

01:03:22.946 --> 01:03:25.448
That was fast, wasn't it?

01:03:25.949 --> 01:03:26.991
Aren't you tired?

01:03:27.492 --> 01:03:30.035
I mean, I told you to go home and rest,

01:03:30.036 --> 01:03:31.037
but…

01:03:31.746 --> 01:03:35.999
I was actually really sad
that you left.

01:03:38.920 --> 01:03:39.921
What is it?

01:03:40.588 --> 01:03:41.840
Is something wrong?

01:03:42.674 --> 01:03:45.801
I just got a call from the restaurant.

01:03:45.802 --> 01:03:47.262
What restaurant?

01:04:01.067 --> 01:04:04.070
I think you owe me an explanation.

01:04:29.179 --> 01:04:31.221
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:04:55.246 --> 01:04:59.833
It sounds like
they're not meant to be together.

01:04:59.834 --> 01:05:03.420
Can you tell me what you know
about what happened seven years ago?

01:05:03.421 --> 01:05:05.672
I'll tell her everything

01:05:05.673 --> 01:05:08.383
and apologize to her.

01:05:08.384 --> 01:05:12.763
The chance
of Ms. Song and I dating is zero.

01:05:12.764 --> 01:05:17.476
Am I really just mistaken
about all those situations?

01:05:17.477 --> 01:05:20.062
It's rare to find
someone who makes you smile.

01:05:20.063 --> 01:05:22.105
What if you're not okay?

01:05:22.106 --> 01:05:23.732
What if something else happens?

01:05:23.733 --> 01:05:26.318
I want to stay by her side,

01:05:26.319 --> 01:05:28.112
but I don't know what to do.

01:05:40.458 --> 01:05:41.541
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:05:41.542 --> 01:05:42.543
Translated by Juyoung Park
